}}'''The dress'''，又被稱為'''藍黑白金裙'''，是一张于2015年2月26日成为[[網路爆紅事物|网络爆红事物]]的照片。該圖片是一件普通的洋裝，主要的爭議點在於該件裙子的顏色究竟是「白色與金色」或是「黑色與藍色」。這種現象揭示了人類色覺的差異，並已成為[[神經科學|神經科學]]和{{Le|視覺科學|Vision science}}正在進行的科研主題，許多論文已在同行評議的科學雜誌上發表。

这张照片起源于一张在[[社交网络服务|社交网络服务]][[Tumblr|Tumblr]]流传的[[连衣裙|连衣裙]]褪色照片。在它开始变得知名的第一周中，有超过1千万个使用了如#thedress、#whiteandgold和#blackandblue的[[主題標籤|主題標籤]]，以提及该连衣裙。即使后来连衣裙的实际颜色已确认为黑色與藍色<ref name="independent">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/the-dress-actual-colour-brand-and-price-details-revealed-10074686.html|title=The blue and black (or white and gold) dress: Actual colour, brand, and price details revealed|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2015-02-27|work=The Independent|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216060750/http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/the-dress-actual-colour-brand-and-price-details-revealed-10074686.html|archivedate=2017-12-16}}</ref><ref name="bbcoptical">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-highlands-islands-31656935|title=Optical illusion: Dress color debate goes global|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=|publisher=BBC|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419045236/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-highlands-islands-31656935|archivedate=2018-04-19}}</ref>，该图片仍然激起了广泛讨论，网友们针对他们对颜色的看法和原因进行讨论。科学界成员开始調查照片以了解人類[[彩色视觉|彩色视觉]]的新見解。

连衣裙本身为设计师Roman Originals的产品，此事件導致连衣裙的銷售大幅增加。设计师之后也为慈善运动设计了白色與金色的连衣裙。

==起源==
葛蕾丝（Grace）和基爾·約翰斯頓（Keir Johnston）在[[蘇格蘭|蘇格蘭]][[科倫賽島|科倫賽島]]进行婚礼的一个星期前，新娘的母亲，塞西莉亞·宝仕德（Cecilia Bleasdale）拍了一张她计划穿去婚礼的[[连衣裙|连衣裙]]并发送给女儿。新娘对照片中连衣裙的颜色看法不同，于是将照片发布在[[Facebook|Facebook]]，她的朋友对颜色也持有不同看法，一些认为是带着金色蕾丝的白色连衣裙，而其他则认为是带着黑色蕾丝的蓝色连衣裙<ref name="wp-insidestory">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/02/27/the-inside-story-of-the-white-dress-blue-dress-drama-that-divided-a-nation/|title=The inside story of the 'white dress, blue dress' drama that divided a planet|author=|date=|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=2018-06-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180521231709/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/02/27/the-inside-story-of-the-white-dress-blue-dress-drama-that-divided-a-nation/|archivedate=2018-05-21}}</ref><ref name="buzzfeed-blueandblack">{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/claudiakoerner/the-dress-is-blue-and-black-says-the-girl-who-saw-it-in-pers|title=The Dress Is Blue And Black, Says The Girl Who Saw It in Person|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=|publisher=|website=BuzzFeed|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530001048/https://www.buzzfeed.com/claudiakoerner/the-dress-is-blue-and-black-says-the-girl-who-saw-it-in-pers|archivedate=2018-05-30}}</ref>。一个星期内，此辩论在科倫賽島开始知名起来<ref name="etonline.com">{{Cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/160575_ellen_degeneres_settles_the_great_dress_debate_once_and_for_all/|title=Ellen DeGeneres Settles the Great Dress Debate Once and For All!|accessdate=|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Entertainment Tonight|access-date=2018-06-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330211614/http://www.etonline.com/news/160575_ellen_degeneres_settles_the_great_dress_debate_once_and_for_all/|archivedate=2016-03-30}}</ref>。

婚礼当天，新娘和新郎的朋友塞特林·麥克尼爾（Ceitlin McNeill）在科倫賽島的婚礼中与她的乐队进行表演。即使亲眼看见该裙子“明显是蓝色和黑色”后<ref name="buzzfeed-blueandblack" />，音乐家们仍然对照片展開討論；她们表示因沉陷于讨论连衣裙的事情而差点没能上台表演。几天后的2月26日，麥克尼爾将照片重新发布在[[Tumblr|Tumblr]]，并向关注她的人问了同样的问题，导致更广大的公众开始讨论此图片<ref name=wp-insidestory/><ref name="buzzfeed-blueandblack" />。

==反应==
===最初的流传过程===
在[[BuzzFeed|Buzzfeed]]的[[紐約|紐約]]辦事處運行其Tumblr頁面的凱茨·霍爾德內斯（Cates Holderness）留意到麥克尼爾请求网友帮助解决连衣裙颜色争辩的信息。当时她忽视了该信息，但当她在工作日即将结束时再次查看页面后，发现该信息当时已获得了5000热度，她表示这对Tumblr来说“是非常爆红的」，Tumblr的數據總監，湯姆·克莱斯（Tom Christ）表示该页面最高获得了每秒1.4万次查看数（或是每分钟84万次查看数），远超过了网站内容的普通速率。当天晚上，热度总数已增加了十倍<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post">{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/charliewarzel/226-how-two-runaway-llamas-and-a-dress-gave-us-the-internets|title=2/26: The Oral History|author=|last=Warzel|first=Charlie|date=2015-02-26|work=|newspaper=[[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]]|accessdate=2018-06-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180319033110/https://www.buzzfeed.com/charliewarzel/226-how-two-runaway-llamas-and-a-dress-gave-us-the-internets|archivedate=2018-03-19}}</ref>。

霍爾德內斯将照片展示给网站的社会媒体队伍中的其他成员，他们马上开始互相争论连衣裙的颜色。她给网友创建了一个简单的投票后便离开工作地点并搭[[紐約地鐵|地铁]]回到她在[[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]的家。当她下地铁并查看手机时，手机已遭不同网站的信息覆没。“我一直都开不了[[Twitter|Twitter]]，因为它一直不断停止运作。我以为可能有谁过世了。我并不知道当时到底发生了什么事。”当天下午，网站在BuzzFeed创出了並發訪問者数量的新纪录，达到了67.3万访问者的最高峰<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" /><ref name="BBCNews1January2016">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-35073088|title=#TheDress couple: 'we were completely left out from the story'|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2016-01-01|publisher=BBC News|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210130745/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-35073088|archivedate=2017-12-10}}</ref>。{{Quote box
 |quote = 对我来说最有趣的事情，就是它紅遍了全球。其从纽约的Twitter小圈子紅到了全球。你可以从我的Twitter通知中看出此事，因为人们开始用不同的语言交流，像是西班牙语、葡萄牙语、日语、中文、泰语和阿拉伯语。看着这件事从一件本地事情演变成巨型国际现象实在是令人驚詫<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。
 |author= – 凱茨·霍爾德內斯
 |source= |align=left |width=300px |qalign=left |salign=right
}}

爆红照片开始成為跨社交媒體的全球[[網路迷因|網路迷因]]。Twitter用户们创建了'''thedress'''、'''#whiteandgold'''、'''#blueandblack'''、 '''#dressgate'''等[[主題標籤|主題標籤]]以讨论连衣裙的颜色并讲解他们对此的推理和看法<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/66892-what-colors-are-this-dress-white-gold-or-black-blue-the-internet-is-going|title=What Colors Are This Dress? White & Gold or Black & Blue? The Internet Is Going Insane Trying To Find Out – PHOTO|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2015-02-26|last=Klassen|first=Anna|publisher=Bustle|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821212542/https://www.bustle.com/articles/66892-what-colors-are-this-dress-white-gold-or-black-blue-the-internet-is-going|archivedate=2017-08-21}}</ref>。关于连衣裙的推文数量于夜间增加；[[美国东部时间|美国东部时间]]晚上6:36时，关于连衣裙的推文首次增加，每分钟有五千个推文使用了主題標籤#TheDress。到晚上8:31时增至每分钟1.1万个推文<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。照片也引起了關於整個事件的討論；《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》形容此争论为一场“分裂星球的戏剧”<ref name="wp-insidestory" /><ref name="bostoncom-colorbind">{{cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/news/nation/2015/02/26/this-dress-white-and-gold-right/MxsJKvqOKtV4lMg84ffNEM/story.html|title=Color Bind: This Dress is White and Gold, Right?|author=|date=|work=Boston Globe|accessdate=2018-06-08|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305052732/http://www.boston.com/news/nation/2015/02/26/this-dress-white-and-gold-right/MxsJKvqOKtV4lMg84ffNEM/story.html|archivedate=2016-03-05}}</ref><ref name="slate-whiteandgold">{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2015/02/26/the_great_blue_and_black_versus_white_and_gold_dress_debate.html|title=The Official Live Blog: Is This Dress Blue and Black or White and Gold?|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Slate|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420192420/http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2015/02/26/the_great_blue_and_black_versus_white_and_gold_dress_debate.html|archivedate=2018-04-20}}</ref>。一些文章则幽默地建议这起事件应對視覺和[[現實|現實]]的本質提出“{{Le|存在主義危機|existential crisis}}”，不然这起争论会伤害人际关系<ref name="wp-insidestory" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/kirstenking/this-dress-is-taking-over|title=This Dress Is Ruining People's Lives|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2015-02-26|last=King|first=Kirsten|publisher=|website=BuzzFeed|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530001059/https://www.buzzfeed.com/kirstenking/this-dress-is-taking-over|archivedate=2018-05-30}}</ref>。其他文章也调查人们针对这类小事造出如此巨大的争议的原因<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/feb/27/colour-dress-optical-illusion-social-media|title=Why do we care about the colour of the dress?|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2015-02-27|work=The Guardian|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821125835/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/feb/27/colour-dress-optical-illusion-social-media|archivedate=2017-08-21}}</ref>。

===一夜爆红===
当天下午，[[维斯理学院|维斯理学院]]的[[神经科学家|神经科学家]]{{Le|貝維爾·康維|Bevil Conway}}向《[[连线|连线]]》的记者亞當·羅傑斯（Adam Rogers）发表了一些关于此现象的评论。在他们挂断电话前，罗杰斯警告他“你的明天再也不会是一样的”。康维以为记者是在夸大其词，就说“我不明白即將發生的事情的全部程度。 差遠了”。罗杰斯的故事最终获得了3280萬次访问。同时，隔天早上康威起床后，他的收件箱受到了大量关于连衣裙的邮件，让他起初误以为邮件已被入侵，直到他发现大量邮件为来自重大媒體組織的采访请求。康维表示“当天我接受了10场采访，还必须让我的同事代我上课”<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。

拥有更多Twitter粉丝的知名人物一夜之间也开始积极参与。[[泰勒·斯威夫特|泰勒·斯威夫特]]在Twitter发布贴文表示她认为连衣裙为蓝色与黑色时整件事让她感到“混乱和害怕”，此推文之后被转推了111,134次并且被按赞了154,188次<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。[[贾登·史密斯|贾登·史密斯]]、[[弗蘭奇·莫尼茲|弗蘭奇·莫尼茲]]、[[黛咪·洛瓦特|黛咪·洛瓦特]]、{{Le|明蒂·卡琳|Mindy Kaling}}和[[贾斯汀·比伯|贾斯汀·比伯]]都赞同连衣裙是蓝色与黑色的，而[[安娜·姬妲妮|安娜·姬妲妮]]、[[B·J·诺瓦克|B·J·诺瓦克]]、[[凱蒂·佩芮|凱蒂·佩芮]]、[[茱莉安·摩爾|茱莉安·摩爾]]與[[莎拉·海蘭|莎拉·海蘭]]则认为是白色与金色<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2091624/dress-blue-black-white-gold-kim-kardashian-miley-cyrus-justin-bieber/|title=What Colors Are This Dress? Kim Kardashian, Miley Cyrus, Justin Bieber and a Bajillion Other Celebs Weigh In|publisher=MTV News|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150401070135/http://www.mtv.com/news/2091624/dress-blue-black-white-gold-kim-kardashian-miley-cyrus-justin-bieber/|archivedate=2015-04-01|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>。[[金·卡戴珊|金·卡戴珊]]发布推文表示她看到了白色与金色，不过她的丈夫[[肯伊·威斯特|肯伊·威斯特]]却看到了蓝色与黑色。[[露西·黑尔|露西·黑尔]]、[[菲比·托金|菲比·托金]]和{{Le|凱蒂·諾蘭|Katie Nolan}}在不同的时间看出了不同的颜色。[[Lady_Gaga|Lady Gaga]]形容连衣裙的颜色为“[[長春花色|長春花色]]与沙黄色”，而[[大衛·杜考夫尼|大衛·杜考夫尼]]则称其为[[藍綠色|藍綠色]]。其他像是[[艾倫·狄珍妮|艾倫·狄珍妮]]和[[爱莉安娜·格兰德|爱莉安娜·格兰德]]的名人也在社交媒体中提到了连衣裙，但并没有提及任何特定颜色<ref name="smh-dressgate">{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/fashion/dressgate-the-white-and-gold-dress-making-our-mind-work-until-its-black-and-blue-20150227-13qqrc.html|title=#Dressgate: The white and gold dress making our mind work until it's black and blue|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|publisher=|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826064331/http://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/fashion/dressgate-the-white-and-gold-dress-making-our-mind-work-until-its-black-and-blue-20150227-13qqrc.html|archivedate=2017-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3725628/the-dress-caitlin-mcneill-post-tumblr-viral/|title=The Dress That Broke the Internet, and the Woman Who Started It All|author=|first1=Rishi|date=|work=|accessdate=2018-06-10|last1=Iyengar|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016150525/http://time.com/3725628/the-dress-caitlin-mcneill-post-tumblr-viral/|archivedate=2017-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://fansided.com/2015/02/26/color-dress-confused-celebrities/|title='What color is this dress' confused celebrities, too|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|publisher=Fansided.com|last1=Sanchez|first1=Josh|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150227193317/http://fansided.com/2015/02/26/color-dress-confused-celebrities/|archivedate=2015-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/28/business/a-simple-question-about-a-dress-and-the-world-weighs-in.html|title=A White and Gold Dress Overloads the Internet|author=|first1=Jonathan|date=|work=|accessdate=2018-06-10|last1=Mahler|website=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180518060252/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/28/business/a-simple-question-about-a-dress-and-the-world-weighs-in.html|archivedate=2018-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3725450/dress-taylor-swift-black-blue-white-gold-celebrities/|title=Taylor Swift Says The Dress is Black and Blue|author=|last=Iyengar|first=Rishi|date=2015-02-26|work=|accessdate=2018-06-10|website=Time|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913193437/http://time.com/3725450/dress-taylor-swift-black-blue-white-gold-celebrities/|archivedate=2017-09-13}}</ref>。政治家、政府機構和知名品牌的社交媒體平台也开着玩笑地加入此事<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/jimdalrympleii/politicians-police-and-brands-have-weighed-in-on-the-dress#.reMRDqg90|title=Politicians, Police, And Brands Have Weighed in On "The Dress"|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=Jim Dalrymple II|date=|publisher=Buzzfeed.com|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171120003112/https://www.buzzfeed.com/jimdalrympleii/politicians-police-and-brands-have-weighed-in-on-the-dress#.reMRDqg90|archivedate=2017-11-20}}</ref>。最终，连衣裙在24小时内成为了440萬个推文的主题<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。

