与连衣裙或甚至是服裝行業一点关系都没有的企业亦在社交媒体上参与了讨论。[[Adobe_Systems|Adobe]]转推了一名使用他们的软件隔离连衣裙颜色的用户。该公司的社交媒体高級經理卡倫·都（Karen Do）回想着说“我们打断了交谈后想，看看会发生什么事吧。”[[必胜客|必胜客]]的高級數碼品牌經理珍娜·布朗伯格（Jenna Bromberg）将连衣裙看成白色与金色后快速地在Twitter发布了一张披萨的图片，表示这个披萨有着一样的颜色。都称其“確實是一个全世界都听到的啁啾聲”<ref name="BuzzFeed anniversary oral history post" />。

《纽约商业杂志》（''New York Business Journal''）的本·菲舍爾（Ben Fischer）报导Buzzfeed的第一篇关于连衣裙的文章所获得的关注程度，并非往常流行事件典型的[[高斯函数|高斯函数]]，而是垂直增長，导致BuzzFeed必须分配两個編輯團隊编写更多关于连衣裙的文章来推動廣告收入<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/newyork/blog/techflash/2015/02/the-dress-phenomenon-didnt-happen-by-accident.html|title=The Dress phenomenon didn't happen by accident. It took big money.|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-02-27|last=Fischer|first=Ben|publisher=American City Business Journals|website=New York Business Journal|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306143147/http://www.bizjournals.com/newyork/blog/techflash/2015/02/the-dress-phenomenon-didnt-happen-by-accident.html|archivedate=2017-03-06}}</ref>，直至3月1日，BuzzFeed的原始文章就获得了超过3.7千万次阅读数<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/catesish/help-am-i-going-insane-its-definitely-blue|title=What Colors Are This Dress?|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-02-26|last=Holderness|first=Cates|publisher=|website=BuzzFeed|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180423060123/https://www.buzzfeed.com/catesish/help-am-i-going-insane-its-definitely-blue|archivedate=2018-04-23}}</ref>。[[有线电视新闻网|有线电视新闻网]]的評論員{{Le|梅爾·羅賓斯 (評論員)|Mel Robbins|梅爾·羅賓斯}}以此事件引证一个流行事件拥有包括“敬畏，歡笑和娛樂”的積極偏見的必要品質，并与当天较早发生的駱馬追逐事件对比，同时在隔天致敬逝世的演员[[伦纳德·尼莫伊|伦纳德·尼莫伊]]<ref name="Robbins">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/02/27/opinion/robbins-llamas-dress/|title=Why blue/black/white/gold dress went viral|author=|first1=Mel|date=2015-02-28|work=|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2018-06-10|last1=Robbins|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180516174142/https://www.cnn.com/2015/02/27/opinion/robbins-llamas-dress/|archivedate=2018-05-16}}</ref>。

===真实的颜色===
連衣裙的设计师Roman Originals之后确认了其为皇室藍“蕾絲緊身連衣裙”，颜色为黑色與藍色<ref name="independent"/><ref name=bbcoptical/>；虽然设计师也设计了其他三种颜色的连衣裙（红色、粉红色和乳白色，各带着黑色蕾丝），但当时并没有设计白色與金色的连衣裙。McNeil发布贴文的隔天，Roman Originals的网站流量开始大幅增加；设计师代表表示“连衣裙在我们营业日的首30分钟就已经售罄，补货后就开始疯狂了起来”<ref name="nydn-romanoriginals">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/fashion/thedress-flying-racks-article-1.2131584|title='The Dress' flying off racks following Internet sensation: 'We sold out in the first 30 minutes of our business day'|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Daily News|location=New York|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180521175754/http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/fashion/thedress-flying-racks-article-1.2131584|archivedate=2018-05-21}}</ref>。2月28日，Roman宣布将会为[[喜劇救濟|喜劇救濟]]的慈善拍賣设计白色與金色的连衣裙<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/the-dress-special-edition-made-in-gold-for-comic-relief-charity-auction-10085484.html|title='The Dress' returns in special edition gold and white version for Comic Relief charity auction|accessdate=2018-06-08|author=|date=2015-03-10|publisher=|website=The Independent|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929232008/https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/the-dress-special-edition-made-in-gold-for-comic-relief-charity-auction-10085484.html|archivedate=2017-09-29}}</ref>。

3月3日，[[艾倫·狄珍妮|艾倫·狄珍妮]]让葛蕾丝、基爾、塞特林和西西莉婭作为嘉宾登场于[[艾倫·狄珍妮秀|艾倫·狄珍妮秀]]。在狄珍妮揭露她觉得连衣裙是白色与金色后，她送给每一位嘉宾一套和连衣裙图案相似但结合两种颜色搭配的内衣，而因Johnstons为了参与节目而提早结束[[蜜月|蜜月]]假期，节目赞助商给了他们$10,000现金以及到[[格林纳达|格林纳达]]的蜜月旅行<ref name="etonline.com" />。

直至3月1日，超过三分之二的BuzzFeed用户投票回复连衣裙是白色与金色<ref name=":0" />。一些人暗示连衣裙会自行更换颜色<ref name="wp-insidestory" />。媒体公司表示照片只是过度[[曝光|曝光]]并且有着粗劣的[[色彩平衡|色彩平衡]]，导致连衣裙的颜色显得褪色，让更多人误以为连衣裙是白色与金色<ref name="wp-insidestory" /><ref name="mashable-overexposed">{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2015/02/26/dress-white-gold-blue-black/|title=Why that dress looks white and gold: It's overexposed|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Mashable|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420111244/https://mashable.com/2015/02/26/dress-white-gold-blue-black/|archivedate=2018-04-20}}</ref>。

== 科學見解 ==
[[File:Wikipe-tan wearing The Dress reduced.svg|thumb|right|连衣裙可依两种方法理解：<br />* 黄色照明下的黑色和蓝色连衣裙（左图）或<br />* 蓝色照明下的白色和金色连衣裙（右图）
]]
[[神经科学家|神经科学家]]{{Le|貝維爾·康維|Bevil Conway}}和{{Le|傑·奈茨|Jay Neitz}}认为之所以出现不同的看法是因人脑[[彩色视觉|看待颜色]]的方式和{{Le|色適應|Chromatic adaptation}}而导致的。康维认为这与人脑如何处理[[日光|白天]]天空的各种色彩有某种联系：“你的視覺系統正在看着这个东西，而你正尝试忽略日光軸的色差。人们不是忽略蓝色的一面，最后看到白色和金色，就是忽略金色的一面，最后看到蓝色和黑色”<ref name="wired-science">{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/02/science-one-agrees-color-dress/|title=The Science of Why No One Agrees on the Color of This Dress|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Wired|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228232822/http://www.wired.com/2015/02/science-one-agrees-color-dress/|archivedate=2015-02-28}}</ref><ref name="theguardian1">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/may/14/thedress-have-researchers-solved-the-mystery-of-its-colour|title=#TheDress: have researchers solved the mystery of its colour?|last=Sample|first=Ian|work=The Guardian|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128234942/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/may/14/thedress-have-researchers-solved-the-mystery-of-its-colour|archivedate=2016-11-28|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>。奈茨说：

<blockquote>我们的视觉系统应当摒弃发光体的信息，并且提取真实的反射率信息……但在我研究色彩视觉之个体差异的30年中，这是我看过最大的个体差异<ref name="wired-science" />。</blockquote>

[[利物浦大学|利物浦大学]]的保羅·諾克斯（Paul Knox）也详细解释了类似的推理，他认为展示照片的设备或观看者自己的期望可能会影响人脑把颜色解释为什么<ref name="Viewpoint">{{cite web|url=http://news.liv.ac.uk/2015/02/27/viewpoint-blue-black-white-gold/|title=Viewpoint: Blue and black or white and gold?|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|publisher=News.liv.ac.uk|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150302025056/http://news.liv.ac.uk/2015/02/27/viewpoint-blue-black-white-gold/|archivedate=2015-03-02}}</ref>。

[[File:Duck-Rabbit_illusion.jpg|thumb]]，在[[路德维希·维特根斯坦|路德维希·维特根斯坦]]的《[[哲学研究|哲学研究]]》中被形容]]

神经科学家兼心理学家帕斯卡爾·瓦利斯赫（Pascal Wallisch）表示虽然模棱刺激在{{Le|視覺科學|Vision science}}多年以来就已固有，但这是第一个社交媒体引起科学界注意的色域刺激。他认为知觉的不同是照明的差異和織物先驗所为，但他也表示刺激物是非常罕見的，因為大多數人的知觉并不會改變。如果改变的话，也只会在很長的時間範圍內出現，这在雙穩態刺激是非常罕见的，因此感知學習可能正在發揮作用<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/health_and_science/science/2015/02/what_color_is_this_dress_a_scientist_explains_visual_ambiguity_and_color.html|title=An experts lesson from the dress|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-03-02|work=Slate|publisher=|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420194722/http://www.slate.com/articles/health_and_science/science/2015/02/what_color_is_this_dress_a_scientist_explains_visual_ambiguity_and_color.html|archivedate=2018-04-20}}</ref>。除此之外，他说明對這種刺激的討論並不是輕浮的，因為此现象既是科學的興趣，又是一個範例，說明不同的人能夠以不同的方式真誠地看待世界，承認這是世界和平的先決條件<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pensees.pascallisch.net/?p=1901|title=Why discussing the dress is not frivolous|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-03-02|publisher=pascallisch.net|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150303112508/http://pensees.pascallisch.net/?p=1901|archivedate=2015-03-03}}</ref>。{{Le|視光師學院|College of Optometrists}}的丹尼爾·哈代曼-麥卡特尼（Daniel Hardiman-McCartney）表示这张照片引起歧义，暗示着這種錯覺是由強烈的黃色光照到衣服上，以及人們通過將圖片中的其他顏色和物體與衣服和光源的顏色進行比較，來感知衣服和光源的顏色而引起的<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.college-optometrists.org/the-college/blogs/-thedress-and-your-optometrist-.html|title=#Thedress and your optometrist – the scientific voice of reason|accessdate=|author=|date=2015-03-02|last=Hardiman-McCartney|first=Daniel|publisher=College of Optometrists|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307050318/https://www.college-optometrists.org/the-college/blogs/-thedress-and-your-optometrist-.html|archivedate=2017-03-07}}</ref>。哲学家{{Le|巴里·C·史密斯|Barry C. Smith}}則将此现象与[[路德维希·维特根斯坦|路德维希·维特根斯坦]]和[[鴨兔錯覺|鸭兔错觉]]对比<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-magazine-monitor-31662317|title=What would Wittgenstein say about that dress?|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-02-27|publisher=BBC|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180207083010/http://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-magazine-monitor-31662317|archivedate=2018-02-07}}</ref>。

一本关于視覺研究的科學雜誌《{{Le|視覺學報|Journal of Vision}}》于2015年3月宣布将会出版一本以《A Dress Rehearsal for Vision Science》为名的关于连衣裙的特别期刊。科學工作目前仍在进行中<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visionscience.com/pipermail/visionlist/2015/008364.html|title=Journal of Vision – Special Issue on The Dress|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-03-12|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509045154/http://www.visionscience.com/pipermail/visionlist/2015/008364.html|archivedate=2015-05-09|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jov.arvojournals.org/SS/thedress.aspx|title=A Dress Rehearsal for Vision Science|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=|work=jov.arvojournals.org|publisher=|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401144459/http://jov.arvojournals.org/SS/thedress.aspx|archivedate=2018-04-01}}</ref>。照片开始流行起来的三个月后，《[[當代生物學|當代生物學]]》發表了第一个关于连衣裙的大規模科學研究。研究中包括了1,400位受訪者，其中57%将连衣裙看成了蓝色与黑色；30%看成了白色与金色；10%看成了黑色和褐色；而10%能够看到不同的颜色<ref name="lafer-sousa">{{cite journal|title=Striking individual differences in color perception uncovered by 'the dress' photograph|author=|url=http://www.cell.com/current-biology/abstract/S0960-9822(15)00535-7|date=2015-06-29|journal=Current Biology|issue=13|doi=10.1016/j.cub.2015.04.053|others=|year=|volume=25|page=|pages=R545–R546|pmc=4921196|pmid=25981795|author3=Bevil R. Conway|author1=Rosa Lafer-Sousa|author2=Katherine L. Hermann|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>。小数量的受访者看成了蓝色与金色。特别多女性和老人看成了白色与金色。研究人员之后发现如果连衣裙是在人造黄色光线下展示的话，几乎所有受访者会看成黑色和蓝色，而如果照明具有藍色偏差的话，他们就会看成白色与金色<ref name="theguardian1" /><ref name="lafer-sousa" /><ref name="gegenfurtner">{{cite journal|title=The many colours of 'the dress'|author=|url=http://www.cell.com/current-biology/abstract/S0960-9822(15)00494-7|date=2015-06-29|journal=Current Biology|issue=13|doi=10.1016/j.cub.2015.04.043|others=|year=|volume=25|page=|pages=R543–R544|pmid=25981790|author3=Matteo Toscani|author1=Karl R. Gegenfurtner|author2=Marina Bloj|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref><ref name="winkler">{{cite journal|title=Asymmetries in blue–yellow color perception and in the color of 'the dress'|author=|url=http://www.cell.com/current-biology/abstract/S0960-9822(15)00542-4|date=2015-06-29|journal=Current Biology|issue=13|doi=10.1016/j.cub.2015.05.004|others=|year=|volume=25|page=|pages=R547–R548|pmc=4489998|pmid=25981792|author3=John S. Werner|author4=Michael A. Webster|author1=Alissa D. Winkler|author2=Lothar Spillmann|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>。《视觉学报》中另一个由帕斯卡爾·瓦利斯赫进行的研究显示早起者更傾向於认为此连衣裙被自然光照着，因此看成了白色和金色，而夜貓子则会看成蓝色与黑色<ref>{{cite journal|title=Illumination assumptions account for individual differences in the perceptual interpretation of a profoundly ambiguous stimulus in the color domain: "The dress"|author=|url=|first1=Pascal|date=2017-04-07|journal=Journal of Vision|issue=4|doi=10.1167/17.4.5|others=|year=|volume=17|page=|pages=5|pmid=|last1=Wallisch}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/health_and_science/science/2017/04/here_s_why_people_saw_the_dress_differently.html|title=Two Years Later, We Finally Know Why People Saw "The Dress" Differently|author=|first1=Pascal|date=2017-04-12|work=[[Slate|Slate]]|accessdate=2018-06-10|last1=Wallisch|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116221825/http://www.slate.com/articles/health_and_science/science/2017/04/here_s_why_people_saw_the_dress_differently.html|archivedate=2018-01-16}}</ref>。

施拉夫基（Schlaffke）等人的科学研究则显示将连衣裙看成白色与金色的人们会增加大腦的額葉和頂葉區域的活动。这些区域被认为在更高的認知活動中至關重要<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/science/2016/03/15/dressgate-if-you-saw-that-dress-as-white-your-brain-was-working/|title=Dressgate: If you saw THAT dress as white your brain was working overtime|last1=Knapton|first1=Sarah|website=The Telegraph|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180402101325/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/science/2016/03/15/dressgate-if-you-saw-that-dress-as-white-your-brain-was-working/|archivedate=2018-04-02|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The brain's dress code: How The Dress allows to decode the neuronal pathway of an optical illusion|author=|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0010945215003226|first1=Lara|date=2015年12月|journal=Cortex|issue=|doi=|others=|year=|volume=73|page=|pages=271-275|pmid=26478963|last1=Schlaffke|access-date=2018-06-10|archive-date=2019-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830183744/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0010945215003226|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==後續==
這件衣服有效地吸引了在線網絡的集體關注；在南非，[[救世軍|救世军]]試圖將這種大眾意識的一部分重新轉向家庭暴力問題<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/trending/salvation-army-uses-the-dress-in-ad-targeting-violence-against-women-1.2985043|title=Salvation Army uses The Dress in ad targeting violence against women|accessdate=2018-06-10|author=|date=2015-03-06|publisher=CBC News|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180202092423/http://www.cbc.ca/news/trending/salvation-army-uses-the-dress-in-ad-targeting-violence-against-women-1.2985043|archivedate=2018-02-02}}</ref>。

作為引發流行現象的照片的原作者，宝仕德和她的配偶保羅·吉克斯（Paul Jinks）之后表示沮喪并痛惜被“完全從故事中排除”，包括他們缺乏對故事的控制，他們作为發現者的疏忽，以及照片的商業用途。他们之后聘请了一名訴狀律師并考虑採取法律行動以保護他們在圖片中的版權<ref name=BBCNews1January2016/>。

2015年，此事件被列入多個知名网络爆红事件的年終名單<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/gallery/memes-biggest-2015/2403468_dress|title=The 15 Best Memes of 2015|accessdate=|author=|date=|publisher=|website=Entertainment Weekly's EW.com|access-date=2018-06-10|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314043417/http://www.ew.com/gallery/memes-biggest-2015/2403468_dress|archivedate=2016-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2681341/best-memes-took-internet-by-storm-in-2015/|title=24 Memes That Took The Internet By Storm in 2015|accessdate=|author=|date=|publisher=MTV News|access-date=2018-06-10|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402032532/http://www.mtv.com/news/2681341/best-memes-took-internet-by-storm-in-2015/|archivedate=2016-04-02}}</ref>。它也出現在[[Google|Google]]當年的年度回顧《Google - Year In Search 2015》當中。

